f indigenous Turkish detective fiction written between 1928 and 1945 attempted to aid in this process of transmission. Five series of this period are carefully analysed; the clear conclusion is that there was authorial intent to spread ideas of “Turkism” in each and every series.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDetective and mystery stories, TurkishxHistory and criticism. 0aHeroes in literature. 0aNational characteristics, Turkish, in literature. 0aNationalism in literature. 0aTurkish fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aTurkish fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161811629140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618116291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618116291.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK